			 <h1 class="shead-style text-center" style="font-size: 4em;">ARUNACHAL PRADESH</h1>
        <p>The largest among the seven northeastern states Arunachal Pradesh is one of premier tourist destination in the northeastern region.  Known as orchid state of India and Paradise of the botanists it is a mountainous state. Many of the tributaries of Brahmaputra flow through it. Most of the stateâ€™s land is covered with forests. As most part of the state is covered with continuous forest lands many different kinds of flora and fauna are present. </p><p>
As most part of the state is unexplored the state possesses a great tourism potential. A state perfect for adventure activities attracts visitors throughout the year. A state rich with Buddhist culture and traditions is an important land for Buddhists. Housing a number of wildlife sanctuaries and reserve forests it is definitely a place worth visiting.
</p>
				
